io.spine.base

Interface RejectionMessage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    EventMessage, KnownMessage, com.google.protobuf.Message, com.google.protobuf.MessageLite, com.google.protobuf.MessageLiteOrBuilder, com.google.protobuf.MessageOrBuilder, java.io.Serializable, SerializableMessage

    @Immutable
public interface RejectionMessage
extends EventMessage
    A common interface for rejection messages.

    This interface is used by the Model Compiler for marking rejection messages. By convention, rejection messages are defined in a proto file, which name ends with rejections.proto.
